    "name": "Helicoprion",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The helicoprion is a bizarre beast to behold. The remarkable physiology of its mouth allows it to f lick out its bottom jaw, unrolling the whorl of teeth and snaring prey along its length. As its powerful muscles roll its jaw, the prey becomes trapped in a spiral of ragged, brutal incisors. Once it has captured a hearty meal, the helicoprion retreats in a thickening cloud of its victim\u2019s blood to patiently await the slowing of struggles and the imminent demise of its dinner."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This creature resembles an ordinary shark from tail to mouth, but the unusual shape of its lower jaw marks it as something else. A whorl of teeth spirals inward, tiny at the centre, but long and brutal farther out.</i>",
